<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="5" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[264,1323,1543,1889]" box="[264,383,1543,1568]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis box="[264,383,1543,1568]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[264,1323,1543,1889]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Moderate sized flies, male body length 
<quantity box="[816,965,1583,1609]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" metricValueMax="7.7" metricValueMin="5.3" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" unit="mm" value="6.5" valueMax="7.7" valueMin="5.3">5.3–7.7 mm</quantity>
(n= 
<number box="[1023,1052,1583,1609]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="15.0">15</number>
), female 
<quantity box="[1175,1323,1583,1609]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.15" metricValueMax="9.8" metricValueMin="6.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" unit="mm" value="8.15" valueMax="9.8" valueMin="6.5">6.5–9.8 mm</quantity>
(n= 
<number box="[308,339,1623,1649]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="14.0">14</number>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[264,1323,1543,1889]" lastBlockId="4.[264,1324,284,1873]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="5" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,385,1662,1688]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Head.</emphasis>
Ocellar tubercle dark reddish brown, not raised above level of vertex in males; setae dark brown, elongate. Eyes dark reddish brown, dichoptic; male ommatidia of equal size. Frons broad in both sexes, setae extending lateral to antennal base; black pruinescent band absent lateral to antennal base. Face projecting moderately beyond anterior margin of eyes. Antenna shorter than head length; scape cylindrical, longer than wide, greater than two times length of pedicel, subequal to width of flagellum, setae present medially on scape and pedicel, macrosetae dark reddish brown; pedicel globular, wider than long, setae dark brown, short; flagellum three segmented, first flagellomere oval, second flagellomere short, cylindrical, third flagellomere cylindrical, rounded apically, style spine­like, set in subapical cavity (
<figureCitation box="[477,548,404,430]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="6.[264,382,1596,1620]" captionTargetBox="[294,1317,313,1573]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[267,1351,303,1603]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Microthereva argentiventris. 1. Antenna. 2. Tergite 8, epandrium, cerci, hypoproct, dorsal view. 3. Sternite 8, gonocoxite, ventral view. 4. Gonocoxite, dorsal view. 5. Gonocoxite, lateral view. 6. Gonostylus, lateral view. 7. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 8. Aedeagus, ventral view. 9. Aedeagus, lateral view. 10. Female internal reproductive organs. Scale = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: C = cercus, CD = common duct, DA = dorsal apodeme, Dp = distiphallus, EA = ejaculatory apodeme, Epa = epandrium, F = furca, Gs = gonostylus, Gx = gonocoxite, H = hypandrium, Hpt = hypoproct, Igp = inner gonocoxal process, Sp = spermatheca, Spd = spermathecal duct, SpS = spermathecal sac, SS = sensory seta, S 8 sternite 8, T 8 = tergite 8, VA = ventral apodeme, VL = ventral lobe." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173536/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Fig. 
<number box="[535,548,404,430]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
), flagellum over two times longer than wide, as long as scape. Parafacial setae elongate. Maxillary palpus cylindrical, apex rounded, greater than four times longer than wide. Gena lacking anterodorsal patch of short setae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[264,1324,284,1873]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,412,523,549]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Thorax.</emphasis>
Macrosetae 
<number box="[572,616,524,550]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="4.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="3.0">3–5</number>
np, 
<number box="[677,722,524,550]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3</number>
sa, 
<number box="[778,793,524,550]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="1.0">1</number>
pa, 
<number box="[853,896,524,550]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="2.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="1.0">1–4</number>
dc, 
<number box="[957,972,524,550]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="2.0">2</number>
sc. Vittae dark brown, dull. Postpronotal lobe concolorous with mesonotum. Cervical sclerite lacking setae and macrosetae. Prosternum lacking setae in and around central depression. Pleuron covered with pruinescence; setae elongate on propleuron, anepisternum, katepisternum, laterotergite, and scutellum; presence of setae variable on metanepisternum; absent on proepimeron and metakatepisternum. 
<emphasis box="[719,787,724,749]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Wing.</emphasis>
Length about three times longer than wide; pterostigma dark brown; setulae absent R 
<number box="[753,761,780,794]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="1.0">1</number>
; cell m 
<number box="[850,858,780,794]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="3.0">3</number>
open widely; M 
<number box="[1053,1061,780,794]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="1.0">1</number>
, M 
<number box="[1103,1111,780,794]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="2.0">2</number>
, and M 
<number box="[1202,1210,780,794]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="3.0">3</number>
originate separately from apex of discal cell; cell 
<emphasis box="[736,779,807,832]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">cup</emphasis>
closed, petiolate; anal angle broadly rounded; alula rounded. 
<emphasis box="[440,503,847,872]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Legs.</emphasis>
Coxae dark brown, pruinescence white, dense; setae white, elongate; setae absent on posterior area of midcoxa; hindcoxa with papillate anterior knob. Femora lacking appressed, lanceolate setae on dorsal surface; av 0:0: 
<number box="[971,1021,927,953]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="1.0" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="0.0">0–2</number>
(generally 
<number box="[1154,1167,927,953]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="1.0">1</number>
), pv 0:0: 
<number box="[1273,1320,927,953]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="0.5" valueMax="1.0" valueMin="0.0">0–1</number>
(generally absent). Tibiae dark yellowish brown, apex of foretibia dark brown. Tarsi dark brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[264,1324,284,1873]" lastBlockId="5.[264,781,284,350]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,441,1047,1073]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Abdomen.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[455,659,1047,1072]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Male 
<taxonomicName box="[529,655,1047,1072]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Combretaceae" genus="Terminalia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="4" pageNumber="23" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">terminalia</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Tergite 
<number box="[768,783,1047,1073]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="8.0">8</number>
(
<figureCitation box="[805,895,1047,1073]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="6.[264,382,1596,1620]" captionTargetBox="[294,1317,313,1573]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[267,1351,303,1603]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Microthereva argentiventris. 1. Antenna. 2. Tergite 8, epandrium, cerci, hypoproct, dorsal view. 3. Sternite 8, gonocoxite, ventral view. 4. Gonocoxite, dorsal view. 5. Gonocoxite, lateral view. 6. Gonostylus, lateral view. 7. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 8. Aedeagus, ventral view. 9. Aedeagus, lateral view. 10. Female internal reproductive organs. Scale = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: C = cercus, CD = common duct, DA = dorsal apodeme, Dp = distiphallus, EA = ejaculatory apodeme, Epa = epandrium, F = furca, Gs = gonostylus, Gx = gonocoxite, H = hypandrium, Hpt = hypoproct, Igp = inner gonocoxal process, Sp = spermatheca, Spd = spermathecal duct, SpS = spermathecal sac, SS = sensory seta, S 8 sternite 8, T 8 = tergite 8, VA = ventral apodeme, VL = ventral lobe." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173536/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Figs. 2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[914,944,1047,1073]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 19" captionStartId="10.[264,382,1265,1289]" captionTargetBox="[287,1298,328,1233]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[256,1332,300,1242]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 19. Microthereva variventris. 11. Tergite 8, epandrium, cerci, hypoproct, dorsal view. 12. Sternite 8, gonocoxite, ventral view. 13. Gonocoxite, dorsal view. 14. Gonocoxite, lateral view. 15. Gonostylus, lateral view. 16. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 17. Aedeagus, ventral view. 18. Aedeagus, lateral view. 19. Female internal reproductive organs. Scale = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173537/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">11</figureCitation>
), anterior margin sinuate with sclerotized collar, posterior margin broadly emarginate; median length thick (&gt; 
<quantity box="[1200,1310,1087,1113]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" unit="mm" value="0.05">0.05 mm</quantity>
); one pair of sensory sensillae. Sternite 
<number box="[725,740,1127,1153]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="8.0">8</number>
(
<figureCitation box="[758,843,1127,1153]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="6.[264,382,1596,1620]" captionTargetBox="[294,1317,313,1573]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[267,1351,303,1603]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Microthereva argentiventris. 1. Antenna. 2. Tergite 8, epandrium, cerci, hypoproct, dorsal view. 3. Sternite 8, gonocoxite, ventral view. 4. Gonocoxite, dorsal view. 5. Gonocoxite, lateral view. 6. Gonostylus, lateral view. 7. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 8. Aedeagus, ventral view. 9. Aedeagus, lateral view. 10. Female internal reproductive organs. Scale = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: C = cercus, CD = common duct, DA = dorsal apodeme, Dp = distiphallus, EA = ejaculatory apodeme, Epa = epandrium, F = furca, Gs = gonostylus, Gx = gonocoxite, H = hypandrium, Hpt = hypoproct, Igp = inner gonocoxal process, Sp = spermatheca, Spd = spermathecal duct, SpS = spermathecal sac, SS = sensory seta, S 8 sternite 8, T 8 = tergite 8, VA = ventral apodeme, VL = ventral lobe." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173536/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Figs. 3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[859,889,1127,1153]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 19" captionStartId="10.[264,382,1265,1289]" captionTargetBox="[287,1298,328,1233]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[256,1332,300,1242]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 19. Microthereva variventris. 11. Tergite 8, epandrium, cerci, hypoproct, dorsal view. 12. Sternite 8, gonocoxite, ventral view. 13. Gonocoxite, dorsal view. 14. Gonocoxite, lateral view. 15. Gonostylus, lateral view. 16. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 17. Aedeagus, ventral view. 18. Aedeagus, lateral view. 19. Female internal reproductive organs. Scale = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173537/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">12</figureCitation>
) quadrate, anterior margin truncate; one pair of sensory sensillae. Epandrium (
<figureCitation box="[758,842,1167,1193]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="6.[264,382,1596,1620]" captionTargetBox="[294,1317,313,1573]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[267,1351,303,1603]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Microthereva argentiventris. 1. Antenna. 2. Tergite 8, epandrium, cerci, hypoproct, dorsal view. 3. Sternite 8, gonocoxite, ventral view. 4. Gonocoxite, dorsal view. 5. Gonocoxite, lateral view. 6. Gonostylus, lateral view. 7. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 8. Aedeagus, ventral view. 9. Aedeagus, lateral view. 10. Female internal reproductive organs. Scale = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: C = cercus, CD = common duct, DA = dorsal apodeme, Dp = distiphallus, EA = ejaculatory apodeme, Epa = epandrium, F = furca, Gs = gonostylus, Gx = gonocoxite, H = hypandrium, Hpt = hypoproct, Igp = inner gonocoxal process, Sp = spermatheca, Spd = spermathecal duct, SpS = spermathecal sac, SS = sensory seta, S 8 sternite 8, T 8 = tergite 8, VA = ventral apodeme, VL = ventral lobe." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173536/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Figs. 2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[854,883,1167,1193]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 19" captionStartId="10.[264,382,1265,1289]" captionTargetBox="[287,1298,328,1233]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[256,1332,300,1242]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 19. Microthereva variventris. 11. Tergite 8, epandrium, cerci, hypoproct, dorsal view. 12. Sternite 8, gonocoxite, ventral view. 13. Gonocoxite, dorsal view. 14. Gonocoxite, lateral view. 15. Gonostylus, lateral view. 16. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 17. Aedeagus, ventral view. 18. Aedeagus, lateral view. 19. Female internal reproductive organs. Scale = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173537/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">11</figureCitation>
) broad basally; shorter medially than wide; anterior margin emarginate; posterolateral margin short, not extending beyond cerci; lateral view rectangular. Cercus (
<figureCitation box="[670,758,1247,1273]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="6.[264,382,1596,1620]" captionTargetBox="[294,1317,313,1573]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[267,1351,303,1603]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Microthereva argentiventris. 1. Antenna. 2. Tergite 8, epandrium, cerci, hypoproct, dorsal view. 3. Sternite 8, gonocoxite, ventral view. 4. Gonocoxite, dorsal view. 5. Gonocoxite, lateral view. 6. Gonostylus, lateral view. 7. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 8. Aedeagus, ventral view. 9. Aedeagus, lateral view. 10. Female internal reproductive organs. Scale = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: C = cercus, CD = common duct, DA = dorsal apodeme, Dp = distiphallus, EA = ejaculatory apodeme, Epa = epandrium, F = furca, Gs = gonostylus, Gx = gonocoxite, H = hypandrium, Hpt = hypoproct, Igp = inner gonocoxal process, Sp = spermatheca, Spd = spermathecal duct, SpS = spermathecal sac, SS = sensory seta, S 8 sternite 8, T 8 = tergite 8, VA = ventral apodeme, VL = ventral lobe." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173536/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Figs. 2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[775,804,1247,1273]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 19" captionStartId="10.[264,382,1265,1289]" captionTargetBox="[287,1298,328,1233]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[256,1332,300,1242]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 19. Microthereva variventris. 11. Tergite 8, epandrium, cerci, hypoproct, dorsal view. 12. Sternite 8, gonocoxite, ventral view. 13. Gonocoxite, dorsal view. 14. Gonocoxite, lateral view. 15. Gonostylus, lateral view. 16. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 17. Aedeagus, ventral view. 18. Aedeagus, lateral view. 19. Female internal reproductive organs. Scale = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173537/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">11</figureCitation>
) free, oval; ending distal to posterolateral margin of epandrium. Hypoproct (
<figureCitation box="[664,747,1287,1313]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="6.[264,382,1596,1620]" captionTargetBox="[294,1317,313,1573]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[267,1351,303,1603]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Microthereva argentiventris. 1. Antenna. 2. Tergite 8, epandrium, cerci, hypoproct, dorsal view. 3. Sternite 8, gonocoxite, ventral view. 4. Gonocoxite, dorsal view. 5. Gonocoxite, lateral view. 6. Gonostylus, lateral view. 7. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 8. Aedeagus, ventral view. 9. Aedeagus, lateral view. 10. Female internal reproductive organs. Scale = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: C = cercus, CD = common duct, DA = dorsal apodeme, Dp = distiphallus, EA = ejaculatory apodeme, Epa = epandrium, F = furca, Gs = gonostylus, Gx = gonocoxite, H = hypandrium, Hpt = hypoproct, Igp = inner gonocoxal process, Sp = spermatheca, Spd = spermathecal duct, SpS = spermathecal sac, SS = sensory seta, S 8 sternite 8, T 8 = tergite 8, VA = ventral apodeme, VL = ventral lobe." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173536/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Figs. 2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[758,787,1287,1313]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 19" captionStartId="10.[264,382,1265,1289]" captionTargetBox="[287,1298,328,1233]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[256,1332,300,1242]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 19. Microthereva variventris. 11. Tergite 8, epandrium, cerci, hypoproct, dorsal view. 12. Sternite 8, gonocoxite, ventral view. 13. Gonocoxite, dorsal view. 14. Gonocoxite, lateral view. 15. Gonostylus, lateral view. 16. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 17. Aedeagus, ventral view. 18. Aedeagus, lateral view. 19. Female internal reproductive organs. Scale = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173537/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">11</figureCitation>
